metadata.analysis_context: Comprehensive statistical analysis of Washington Huskies vs Wisconsin Badgers matchup preparation. Data collected from Sports Info Solutions (SIS) API covering multiple aspects of team performance including snap counts, penalties, deep ball passing, explosive plays, Middle 8 performance, and situational targets.

conference.name: Big Ten
conference.description: Big Ten Conference (B1G) - All rankings and comparisons are within this conference

data_quality_notes: All data sourced from SIS API with access level limitations
Some endpoints require premium access (e.g., frametimer endpoints) and were not available
Task 2 (Snap-to-Throw Time) was skipped due to 403 Forbidden errors on frametimer endpoints
Task 5 was not completed as part of this analysis
Penalty data extracted via pattern matching from play descriptions - some details may be incomplete
Big Ten rankings calculated where applicable based on conference membership (conferenceId=3)

schedule_info.description: Team schedules showing which weeks games were actually played. Missing weeks in task data are likely bye weeks (no game scheduled) rather than missing data.

washington.note: If a week is missing from task data, check if it appears in games_played_weeks. If not, it's a bye week (no game that week).

wisconsin.note: If a week is missing from task data, check if it appears in games_played_weeks. If not, it's a bye week (no game that week).

task_1.description: Measures the total number of plays (snaps) for each team in each game, broken down by offensive snaps, defensive snaps, and total snaps.
task_1.methodology: Data collected from SIS API driveinfo_enhanced endpoint. Offensive snaps calculated by summing totalPlays from drives where the team is the offensive team. Defensive snaps calculated by summing totalPlays from drives where the team is the defensive team.

game_date.description: Date and time of the game

offensive_snaps.description: Number of offensive plays (snaps) for the team in this game
offensive_snaps.calculation: Sum of totalPlays from all drives where team is offensiveTeamId

defensive_snaps.description: Number of defensive plays (snaps) for the team in this game
defensive_snaps.calculation: Sum of totalPlays from all drives where team is defensiveTeamId

total_snaps.description: Total number of snaps (offensive + defensive) for the team

task_1.notes: Special teams plays are not separately tracked. Total snaps include all plays from scrimmage.

task_3.description: Detailed breakdown of every penalty called in each game, including penalty type, yards assessed, whether it was accepted or declined, time of game, and player information.
task_3.methodology: Data extracted from SIS API playdescription endpoint by parsing extraNote fields using regular expressions to identify penalty descriptions, types, yards, and acceptance status.

total_penalties.description: Total number of penalties called in the game

opponent_penalties.description: Total penalties called on the opponent

washington_accepted.description: Number of Washington penalties that were accepted (not declined)

washington_yards.description: Total penalty yards assessed against Washington

penalties_detail.description: Array of individual penalty records

time.description: Time remaining in the quarter when penalty occurred

penalty_side.description: Whether penalty was on offense or defense

team_name.description: Name of team that committed the penalty

player_name.description: Name of player who committed the penalty

player_number.description: Jersey number of player who committed the penalty

penalty_type.description: Type of penalty (e.g., Holding, False Start, Pass Interference)

yards.notes: If multiple yard values appear in description, the last one is used (penalty yards come after play description)

accepted.description: Whether the penalty was accepted (true) or declined (false)

task_3.notes: Penalty data is extracted from play descriptions using pattern matching. Some penalty details may be incomplete if not clearly stated in the description.

task_4.description: Analysis of passing plays with 20 or more air yards downfield, including attempts, completions, yards, touchdowns, and Big Ten conference rankings.
task_4.methodology: Data queried from SIS API players/query endpoint using MetricGroup=1 (Passing) with PassingFilters.MinAirYards=20 and TimeFilters.ByGame=1. Also includes receiving stats (MetricGroup=5) with ReceivingFilters.MinAirYards=20.

min_air_yards.description: Minimum air yards threshold for deep ball classification

by_game.description: Statistics broken down by individual game

game_key.description: Composite key identifying the game (format: Week{week}_{opponent})

attempts.description: Number of deep ball pass attempts

completions.description: Number of completed deep ball passes

yards.description: Total passing yards on deep ball attempts

touchdowns.description: Number of touchdown passes on deep ball attempts

interceptions.description: Number of interceptions on deep ball attempts

total.description: Season totals aggregated across all games

big_ten_rank.description: Team's ranking in Big Ten conference for total deep ball attempts
big_ten_rank.notes: Rank 1 = most attempts, higher rank = fewer attempts

receiving_stats.description: Receiving statistics for deep ball targets

by_game.description: Receiving stats broken down by game

top_recipients.description: List of players who received deep ball targets

task_4.notes: Air yards refer to the distance the ball travels in the air, not total yards gained. Rankings are based on total attempts across the season.

task_6.description: Analysis of explosive offensive plays per week, with run/pass breakdown and Big Ten rankings. Explosive plays defined as: pass plays 20+ total yards, rush plays 15+ yards.
task_6.methodology: Data queried from SIS API players/query endpoint using MetricGroup=1 (Passing) and MetricGroup=3 (Rushing) with yardage filters and TimeFilters.ByGame=1. Plays filtered post-query to ensure yardage thresholds are met.

passing_threshold.description: Minimum yards for explosive passing play

rushing_threshold.description: Minimum yards for explosive rushing play

rank.description: Big Ten ranking for this week
Big Ten ranking for this week

task_6.notes: Total yards includes yards after catch for passing plays. Rankings are calculated weekly and may vary by week.

task_7.description: Analysis of explosive plays allowed by the defense per week, with run/pass breakdown and Big Ten rankings. Measures opponent's explosive plays: pass plays 20+ yards, rush plays 15+ yards.
task_7.methodology: Data queried from SIS API players/query endpoint using vsMultipleTeams filter to get opponent offensive stats. Passing stats use MetricGroup=1, rushing stats use MetricGroup=3. Plays matched to defensive teams using schedule data (week + opponent_id).

passing_threshold.description: Minimum yards for explosive passing play allowed

rushing_threshold.description: Minimum yards for explosive rushing play allowed

task_7.notes: Lower numbers are better for defensive statistics. This measures opponent offensive success against the team's defense.

task_8.description: Points scored and allowed during the 'Middle 8' window: last 4 minutes of the first half (Quarter 2, 0:00-4:00 remaining) plus first 4 minutes of the second half (Quarter 3, 11:00-15:00 remaining).
task_8.methodology: Data collected from SIS API driveinfo_enhanced endpoint. Drives are filtered by quarter and startTime to identify scoring drives within the Middle 8 window. Points calculated from drive results: TOUCHDOWN=6, FIELD_GOAL=3, SAFETY=2.

middle_8_definition.value: Last 4 min of 1st half (Q2, 0:00-4:00) + First 4 min of 2nd half (Q3, 11:00-15:00)

points_scored.description: Points scored by the team during Middle 8

points_allowed.description: Points allowed (scored by opponent) during Middle 8

notes: The Middle 8 is a critical game management period. Positive net indicates better performance in these key moments.

Note: Extra points (PATs) are not captured in this analysis. Only touchdowns (6 points), field goals (3 points), and safeties (2 points) from scoring drives are counted. Extra point attempts occur after touchdowns but are tracked as separate plays and are not included in the drive result scoring.

task_9.description: Receiving targets, receptions, first downs, and touchdowns in two critical situations: 3rd down conversions and Red Zone (opponent's 20-yard line to 1-yard line). Includes player-level breakdown by game.
task_9.methodology: Data queried from SIS API players/query endpoint using MetricGroup=5 (Receiving). 3rd down filter: SituationFilters.Downs=3. Red Zone filter: FieldPositionFromSide=1, FieldPositionFromYd=20, FieldPositionToYd=1. TimeFilters.ByGame=1 for per-game data.

big_ten_rankings.description: Big Ten conference rankings for teams and players

third_down.description: All Big Ten teams ranked by 3rd down targets

redzone.description: All Big Ten teams ranked by Red Zone targets

player_rankings.description: Big Ten player rankings by target share

third_down.description: All Big Ten players ranked by 3rd down target share percentage

target_share.description: Player's targets as percentage of team's total 3rd down targets

redzone.description: All Big Ten players ranked by Red Zone target share percentage

target_share.description: Player's targets as percentage of team's total Red Zone targets

task_9.notes: Red Zone defined as opponent's 20-yard line to 1-yard line. Player-level data only includes players with targets > 0 for each game.
